Kafka 0.8 Output Plugin

Building this plugin:
Requires librdkafka, download and install from https://github.com/edenhill/librdkafka.

Omkafka pushes data out of rsyslog into a kafka cluster, the topic can be templated
as well as the message that will be inserted into the log.

This module will output statistics as well; both how many messages it has submitted
and how many have failed.

This plugin requires the v6 format.

Example configuration:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
module(load="imudp")
module(load="omkafka")
module(load="impstats"
       interval="5"
       severity="7")
syslog.=debug /var/log/testingstats
template(name="testmsg" type="string" string="%syslogtag%:%msg%")
template(name="testtopic" type="string" string="%programname%")
ruleset(name="kafkatesting"){
    action(type="omkafka"
           brokers="kafka-broker01:9092"
           topic="testtopic"
           dyntopic="on"
           template="testmsg"
           )
}
input(type="imudp" port="9999" ruleset="kafkatesting")
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The above example, binds to UDP port 9999 and will forward all messages
to kafka using the %programname% property and the messages will be
"%syslogtag%:%msg%". It will also output the stats every 5 seconds so you
can watch those messages fly through!

NOTE: This requires custom configuration to the autoconf/automake options for
rsyslog in general. I will update a gist on github when I make those.

Currently only tested with rsyslog v7.4.7 (CentOS 7). SRPM is available if wanted.
